1. Get penguin data

  • Data: Penguin sizes collected November 2007, Palmer Station Antarctica LTER).

  • Citation: Gorman K. 2017. Structural size measurements and isotopic signatures of foraging among adult male and female Adlie penguins (Pygoscelis adeliae) nesting along the Palmer Archipelago near Palmer Station, 2007-2009. Environmental Data Initiative. http://dx.doi.org/10.6073/pasta/abc50eed9138b75f54eaada0841b9b86. Dataset accessed 1/29/2018.

# Read in data
penguins <- read_csv("penguins.csv")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   species = col_character(),
##   region = col_character(),
##   island = col_character(),
##   date = col_character(),
##   flipper_length = col_integer(),
##   body_mass = col_integer(),
##   sex = col_character()
## )
# Only male penguins
male_p <- penguins %>% 
  filter(sex == "MALE")

# Exploratory graph
ggplot(male_p, aes(x = flipper_length)) +
  geom_histogram(bins = 12) +
  theme_light()

# Pull flipper lengths as a vector
flippers <- male_p %>% 
  pull(flipper_length)

# Create a function to calculate the mean of varying vectors (x) of index (i)
mean_fun <- function (x,i) {mean(x[i])}

# First try - 10 bootstrap samples (silly to do in practice, good for demonstration)
# 10 bootstrap samples: 
boot_10 <- boot(flippers, mean_fun, R = 10)

# Reporting outcomes of bootstrapping: 
boot_10$t # to report means of all 10 bootstrap samples
##           [,1]
##  [1,] 189.8636
##  [2,] 187.3182
##  [3,] 187.5455
##  [4,] 190.6818
##  [5,] 187.7273
##  [6,] 188.3182
##  [7,] 191.4545
##  [8,] 190.0000
##  [9,] 186.7273
## [10,] 189.5000
boot_10$t0 # to report the mean of the original sample
## [1] 188.1818
boot_10

# 100 bootstrap samples: 
boot_100 <- boot(flippers, mean_fun, R = 100)

ggplot() +
  aes(boot_100$t) + 
  geom_histogram()
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

# We can find a confidence interval for our bootstrapped means:

2. Go exploring

boot.ci(boot_100000, conf = 0.95)
